Introduction

Ladies’ Code is a South Korean girl group that debuted under Polaris Entertainment on March 7, 2013, with the mini album Code#01 Bad Girl. Known for their retro-inspired sound, strong vocals, and mature concepts, the group originally gained attention for blending pop hooks with a stylish, throwback edge.

The group’s early success was tragically interrupted in 2014 when members EunB and RiSe passed away following a car accident—an event that deeply affected fans and the industry alike. The surviving members—Ashley, Sojung, and Zuny—returned in 2016 with Myst3ry, shifting to a more introspective and emotional sound.

Over time, Ladies’ Code carved out a unique legacy in K-pop history—remembered for their artistry, resilience, and their ability to grow through unimaginable loss.

Ladies’ Code announced the group will be going on hiatus after their contracts expired on February 17, 2020.
